  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      A multicenter, prospective, controlled, randomized (moderate hypothermia 33°C≤ T°C ≤34°C)
      during 24 hours ± 1h versus normothermia (37°C ± 0.3 °C), comparative open trial will be
      conducted on two parallel groups of patients with cardiogenic shock treated with VA-ECMO.

      The HYPO-ECMO trial will test the hypothesis that moderate hypothermia (temperature between
      33°C≤ T°C ≤34°C) associated with VA-ECMO support results in a reduction in 30-day mortality
      in comparison with the normothermia group (37°C ± 0.3°C).
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
